<h1>Problem 2271 - 2015 CGMO, P6 of 8, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(\Gamma_1\) and \(\Gamma_2\) be two non-overlapping circles. \(A,C\) are on \(\Gamma_1\) and \(B,D\) are on \(\Gamma_2\) such that \(AB\) is an external common tangent to the two circles, and \(CD\) is an internal common tangent to the two circles. \(AC\) and \(BD\) meet at \(E\). \(F\) is a point on \(\Gamma_1\), the tangent line to \(\Gamma_1\) at \(F\) meets the perpendicular bisector of \(EF\) at \(M\). \(MG\) is a line tangent to \(\Gamma_2\) at \(G\). Prove that \(MF=MG\).</p>
